{"id": 223687594, "title": "Belfast nursery \"so proud\" to be named one of the best in Northern Ireland by parents", "text": "A Belfast nursery has shared its pride in being recognised as one of the best in the country. Parents in Northern Ireland have rated Belfast YMCA Nursery & After School as one of the Top 20 nurseries, out of 226 early years settings across the country. As one of the top-rated in the country, Belfast YMCA received an award from the leading day nurseries reviews site, Day Nurseries, with the award based on the nursery\u2019s reviews from the children\u2019s families and carers. The nurseries were rated on overall standard, facilities and outside space, learning, resources and equipment and ICT, care, activities, staff, food and nutrition, management, cleanliness, safeguarding as well as value for money. Read more: NI parents raise \u00a337k to help others after 'most traumatic day' of their lives Sarah Ferguson, Head of Childcare at Belfast YMCA Nursery & After School, said: \u201cBelfast YMCA Nursery and After School are delighted to receive a Top 20 Day Nursery Award. \"We are so proud to be recognised for the high quality care we provide through the hard work and dedication of our staff. \"We are grateful to all the parents who took the time to write a review and we will continue to provide an affordable, flexible and child centred Nursery and Afterschool.\u201d There are over 14,000 nurseries in the UK, with over 400,000 people working in the childcare sector. Around one million children in the UK attend a nursery, ranging in age from three months to five years old. Amanda Hopkins, reviews manager of Day Nurseries said: \u201cWe would like to congratulate Belfast YMCA Nursery & After School on being rated by parents as a top nursery in Northern Ireland! Being rated so highly by family and carers of children that attend the setting is a huge achievement. \u201cOur award is valuable recognition from parents and carers that this nursery is offering their children an excellent standard of care and a stimulating environment, which will help boost their development and hopefully create a lifelong love of learning. \u201cWe hope these awards give parents that much needed guidance in choosing the right nursery for their child.\u201d For all the latest news, visit the Belfast Live homepage here and sign up to our daily newsletter here", "summary": "&quot;We are so proud to be recognised for the high quality care we provide through the hard work and dedication of our staff&quot;", "url": "https://www.belfastlive.co.uk/whats-on/family-kids-news/belfast-nursery-so-proud-named-29241700", "image": "https://i2-prod.belfastlive.co.uk/incoming/article29241677.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_Screenshot-2024-05-26-110745.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 12:37:27", "author": "Sophie Mclaughlin", "authors": ["Sophie Mclaughlin"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": 0.462}